Source: neovim-latest
Section: editors
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Dario Griffo <dariogriffo@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), wget, ca-certificates, xz-utils
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://neovim.io
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: neovim-latest
Architecture: amd64
Depends: neovim-latest-runtime (= ${source:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: python3-pynvim, xxd, xclip | xsel | wl-clipboard
Suggests: ctags
Provides: neovim (= ${source:Upstream-Version}), editor
Conflicts: neovim
Replaces: neovim
Description: heavily refactored vim fork (latest upstream build)
 Neovim is a fork of Vim focused on modern code and features, rather than
 running in legacy environments.
 .
 This package ships the official upstream prebuilt nvim binary (stripped),
 repackaged for Debian so that stable users (bookworm, trixie, ...) can track
 the latest Neovim release as soon as it is published. It provides
 /usr/bin/nvim (and the "editor" alternative) via update-alternatives.

Package: neovim-latest-runtime
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Provides: neovim-runtime (= ${source:Upstream-Version})
Conflicts: neovim-runtime
Replaces: neovim-runtime
Description: heavily refactored vim fork (runtime files)
 Neovim is a fork of Vim focused on modern code and features, rather than
 running in legacy environments.
 .
 This package contains the architecture-independent runtime files (syntax and
 indentation rules, colour schemes, standard plugins, documentation, the man
 page and the desktop entry) shared by the neovim-latest binary packages.

Package: neovim-latest-unstripped
Architecture: amd64
Depends: neovim-latest (= ${source:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: heavily refactored vim fork (unstripped binary)
 Neovim is a fork of Vim focused on modern code and features, rather than
 running in legacy environments.
 .
 This package provides the same upstream nvim binary as neovim-latest but with
 the upstream debug symbols retained, which is useful for backtraces and
 debugging. Install it alongside neovim-latest and switch the active binary
 with: update-alternatives --config nvim
